pageContext.claim: “Nationwide, beyond the outbreak in several states, cases remain low and very stable. Nineteen states have positive test rates of less than 5 percent. Eight states have positive test rates of less than 2 percent. Our nationwide positive test rate is beginning to decline and is currently at 8.8 percent, compared to over 16 percent at its peak in April. It's coming down. It's coming down fairly rapidly.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump kept suggesting the nation was turning the corner on the pandemic, but little progress was being made and the death count kept going up.
